# Pixel-Art Design

## Scaling

Integer scale factors only. Use `image-rendering: pixelated` or `crisp-edges`.

```css
/* ❌ BAD */
.sprite { transform: scale(1.5); }

/* ✅ GOOD */
.sprite { transform: scale(2); image-rendering: pixelated; }
```

## Visual style

- No blur, soft drop-shadows, or gradient-heavy UI (unless explicitly stylistic).
- UI chrome should feel cohesive with the project's game/retro aesthetic, not generic SaaS.
- Colors and fonts from project design tokens — do not invent new brand colors without updating tokens.

## Typography

Use the pixel/bitmap font defined in project design tokens.

## Motion

Stepped keyframe animation at **8–12 fps** feel. No smooth easing on sprite movement.

## Assets

Provide @2x variants or integer scale factors for Retina / high-DPI screens.

## Full-screen views

Respect safe-area insets (notch, home indicator) on immersive screens.

Adjust path globs if the frontend directory differs.
